NEWCASTLE DISEASE, OSTRICH, IMPORTED - BRAZIL (02)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Newcastle disease, ostrich, imported - Brazil 970929151441
Date: Sat, 03 Jan 1998 11:28:41 -0300
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luisjs@guttenberg.correionet.com.br>

According to the Jan 3, 1998 paper edition of "O Estado de Sao Paulo"(p.
A7), a Sao Paulo-based Brazilian daily, the Brazilian Ministry of
Agriculture has imposed a temporary ban on the importation from any country
of ostriches and ornamental birds, including embryonated eggs, as
protection from Newcastle disease and bird influenza. The spokesperson for
the Ministry of Agriculture emphasized that this has nothing to do with the
recent bird influenza episode in Hong Kong.
--
