[The New Zealanders have also recognised this import trade as posing a
possible risk of importing the above infections. Considering the dubious
commercial value and the pyramid schemes associated with ratite species,
the loss to Brazil from this ban is probably slight or even negative.
Plus, in the past a number of North American breeding flocks were afflicted
with avian tuberculosis and the infection went with dispersal and culling
sales. Presumably the same situation occurred elsewhere. - Mod.MHJ
